          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            This is what will happen, coming from an Arsenal fan. We will have the majority of possession (60% +), will have many attacks and likely many chances. None of them will be taken unless we have 10+ on target in which case 1 might sneak in (Sanchez no doubt will score it if so). Wenger will order the defence to defend too high with the wing backs playing as wingers. That in turn will lead to Dortmund scoring at least once on the counter attack. There is also the probability that at a corner, with our terrible zonal marking, 1 of the Dortmund central defenders will have a free header which they may or may not put away. Following our grabbing of a loss from the jaws of victory, Wenger will use the cliché words/phrases "focus", "team spirit" and "belief" in the post-match interview to justify why a loss or (best case scenario) a draw was a good result. He will also fail to see any of the chronic problems in his tactics and get the team to play exactly the same way in the next game.
